verses.text:
Samson said to them, “Let me tell you a riddle now. If you can
tell me the answer within the seven days of the feast, and find it out, then I will give you thirty linen
garments and thirty changes of clothing;

She wept before him the seven days, while their feast lasted;
and on the seventh day, he told her, because she pressed him severely; and she told the riddle to the
children of her people.
